headline: Autodesk Q1 FY26 Earnings: Strong Revenue, Non-GAAP Margin Expansion, and Strategic Initiatives Amidst Macro Caution
summary: Design software company Autodesk (NASDAQ:ADSK) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 15.2% year on year to $1.63 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $2.29 per share was 6.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
